down","description":"South Africa's official unemployment rate fell to 31.4% in Q4 2025 — the lowest since Q2 2022 — as 44,000 more people found work. The number of employed persons rose to 17.1 million. The expanded unemployment rate (including discouraged work-seekers) stands at 40.7%.","source":{"name":"Statistics South Africa","shortName":"Stats SA","url":"https://www.statssa.gov.za/?page_id=1854&PPN=P0211","publicationName":"Quarterly Labour Force Survey Q4 2025","publicationDate":"2026-02-17"},"lastUpdated":"2026-02-17","series":[{"name":"Unemployment Rate (%)","unit":"%","data":[{"label":"Q1 2022","value":34.5},{"label":"Q2 2022","value":33.9},{"label":"Q3 2022","value":32.9},{"label":"Q4 2022","value":32.7},{"label":"Q1 2023","value":32.9},{"label":"Q2 2023","value":33.5},{"label":"Q3 2023","value":33.7},{"label":"Q4 2023","value":32.9},{"label":"Q1 2024","value":32.9},{"label":"Q2 2024","value":33.5},{"label":"Q3 2024","value":32.1},{"label":"Q4 2024","value":31.9},{"label":"Q1 2025","value":33.5},{"label":"Q2 2025","value":33.2},{"label":"Q3 2025","value":31.9},{"label":"Q4 2025","value":31.4}]}]},{"id":"youth-unemployment","categoryId":"unemployment","title":"Youth Unemployment (15–34)","value":"44.8%","rawValue":44.8,"unit":"%","change":-0.9,"changeLabel":"from Q3 2025","trend":"down","description":"Youth unemployment (ages 15–34) declined to 44.8% in Q4 2025. Among those aged 15–24, the rate stands at 61.4% — meaning roughly 6 in 10 young South Africans who want work cannot find it. South Africa's youth unemployment is among the highest globally.","source":{"name":"Statistics South Africa","shortName":"Stats SA","url":"https://www.statssa.gov.za/?page_id=1854&PPN=P0211","publicationName":"Quarterly Labour Force Survey Q4 2025","publicationDate":"2026-02-17"},"lastUpdated":"2026-02-17","series":[{"name":"Youth Unemployment Rate (%)","unit":"%","data":[{"label":"Q1 2022","value":47.4},{"label":"Q2 2022","value":47},{"label":"Q3 2022","value":46},{"label":"Q4 2022","value":45.7},{"label":"Q1 2023","value":46.3},{"label":"Q2 2023","value":47.1},{"label":"Q3 2023","value":47.3},{"label":"Q4 2023","value":46.1},{"label":"Q1 2024","value":45.9},{"label":"Q2 2024","value":46.2},{"label":"Q3 2024","value":44.9},{"label":"Q4 2024","value":45.4},{"label":"Q1 2025","value":46.1},{"label":"Q2 2025","value":45.9},{"label":"Q3 2025","value":45.7},{"label":"Q4 2025","value":44.8}]}]},{"id":"labour-force-participation","categoryId":"unemployment","title":"Labour Force Participation Rate","value":"42.7%","rawValue":42.7,"unit":"%","change":-0.1,"changeLabel":"from Q3 2025","trend":"stable","description":"42.7% of working-age South Africans (ages 15–64) were either employed or actively seeking work in Q4 2025. This participation rate remains among the lowest globally, partly reflecting large numbers of discouraged work-seekers who have given up looking for jobs.","source":{"name":"Statistics South Africa","shortName":"Stats SA","url":"https://www.statssa.gov.za/?page_id=1854&PPN=P0211","publicationName":"Quarterly Labour Force Survey Q4 2025","publicationDate":"2026-02-17"},"lastUpdated":"2026-02-17","series":[{"name":"Participation Rate (%)","unit":"%","data":[{"label":"Q1 2023","value":42.8},{"label":"Q2 2023","value":42.5},{"label":"Q3 2023","value":43.1},{"label":"Q4 2023","value":43.2},{"label":"Q1 2024","value":42.9},{"label":"Q2 2024","value":43},{"label":"Q3 2024","value":43.3},{"label":"Q4 2024","value":42.9},{"label":"Q1 2025","value":42.5},{"label":"Q2 2025","value":42.9},{"label":"Q3 2025","value":42.8},{"label":"Q4 2025","value":42.7}]}]}],"label":"Unemployment","variant":"full","exportMode":"series","className":"w-full justify-center"}]}],["$","$L4",null,{"entry":{"id":"unemployment","label":"Unemployment","description":"Official quarterly unemployment rate (ILO strict definition) from the Stats SA QLFS.","statIds":["unemployment-national","youth-unemployment","labour-force-participation"],"categoryId":"unemployment","